title: Fifth victim of Taiwan amusement park fire succumbs to burns
text:
DPA
Taipei
A fifth burn victim died on Sunday from severe injuries suffered in an explosion at a Taiwanese amusement park two weeks ago, with about 210 others still in critical condition, local media reported.
The 22-year-old woman died on Sunday morning in a hospital of New Taipei, the state-run Central News Agency said.
Su was admitted to the hospital with burns to about 95 percent of her body after a flammable powder exploded over the crowd during a concert on June 27.
The explosion injured hundreds of people, including foreigners from Japan, Singapore, Malaysia, China, and the United States. So far, the accident has claimed the lives of five Taiwanese people aged 19-23.
The Health Ministry on the weekend announced that about 270 people remained in intensive care, with about 210 of them described as being in life-threatening conditions.
A group of six Japanese medical experts was arriving in Taipei on Sunday to offer assistance, the agency said.The cause of the explosion remains under investigation.
